---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const journeyItems = [
  {
    period: "2024 - Present",
    role: "Core Software Engineering",
    details: "Focusing on backend systems and concurrency coordination. Contributing to DailyDine's scheduling backend."
  },
  {
    period: "2023 - 2024",
    role: "Open Source and Linux Fundamentals",
    details: "Began contributing to student developer groups. Focused on mastering Linux command line and system administration."
  },
  {
    period: "2021 - 2023",
    role: "Initial Programming and Exploration",
    details: "Explored programming fundamentals. Focused on basic data structures, algorithms, and script automation."
  }
];
---

<Layout title="About">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[960px] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-20 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-[68ch]">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-none">
        About
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
        A record of motives, operating workflows, and learning logs that guide my growth as an engineer.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Why I Build (Motives) -->
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-10 max-w-[68ch]">
      
      <!-- Why Software -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
          Why Software?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-[1.7]">
          I started programming because I wanted to understand how computers actually work.
          The ability to instruct silicon to coordinate data remains deeply fascinating to me.
          I believe that software engineering is a craft requiring patience, humility, and continuous study.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Why Cybersecurity -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
          Why Cybersecurity?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-[1.7]">
          Building software requires understanding boundaries.
          Studying security forces you to inspect how protocols behave under invalid configurations or malicious loads.
          By studying cybersecurity, I learn to design code that is secure by default and resilient against failures.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Why Writing? -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
          Why Writing?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-[1.7]">
          I do not write because I have mastered systems.
          I write because it is the process through which I analyze and understand them.
          If I cannot write a simple explanation of an architecture, I do not understand the system.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Why Build in Public? -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
          Why Build in Public?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-[1.7]">
          Knowing that other engineers might read your notes forces absolute precision.
          Documenting mistakes, architecture choices, and lessons openly creates a feedback loop
          that refines my development habits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- What Kind of Engineer? -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
          The Kind of Engineer I Want to Become
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-[1.7]">
          I aim to become a craftsman-style systems engineer.
          I value boring, reliable, and clean software architectures that still make sense ten years later.
          I prefer to reduce systems to their absolute essentials to ensure they are easy to maintain and scale.
        </p>
      </div>

    </section>

    <!-- How I Learn -->
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
        How I Learn
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-[#FAFAFA]">Read Manuals First</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
            I study domains by reading raw documentation and specification sheets.
            Going directly to the source material yields complete, unbiased technical clarity.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-[#FAFAFA]">Verify in Labs</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
            I write tiny, isolated scripts to verify how network sockets, databases, or memory buffers behave.
            Verification prevents assumptions about library behavior.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Principles link -->
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4 max-w-[68ch]">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
        Principles
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
        I return to core principles whenever I face architectural complexity.
        These guide my trade-off decisions and keep code maintainable.
      </p>
      <div>
        <a href="/principles" class="text-xs text-[#2563EB] hover:underline font-medium">Read all principles →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Operating Manual -->
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
        Operating Manual
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-[#FAFAFA]">Focus Blocks</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
            I block off dedicated focus windows to study technical manuals.
            I avoid constant context switching to allow deep comprehension.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-[#FAFAFA]">Workflow Integration</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
            I prioritize local-first tools, strict version control, and regression testing.
            The best software lets me focus on thinking rather than configuration.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Journey -->
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
        Journey
      </h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
        {journeyItems.map((item) => (
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-2 sm:gap-12">
            <span class="text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono sm:w-28 flex-shrink-0">{item.period}</span>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-[#FAFAFA]">{item.role}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed max-w-[68ch]">{item.details}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Résumé -->
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4 max-w-[68ch]">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-2">
        Résumé
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
        I maintain a dedicated resume page detailing professional projects, skills, education, and credentials.
      </p>
      <div>
        <a href="/about/resume" class="text-xs text-[#2563EB] hover:underline font-medium">View full résumé →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
